The paper deals with image retrieval using hashing techniques, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves transfer learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and has been applied to various computer vision tasks. The paper also discusses the optimization of hashing functions, which is a key aspect of information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the experiments involve benchmark databases commonly used in multimedia retrieval (cs.MM) and the proposed method involves unsupervised learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
